tape - tape recorder (Mark III drive)
Syntax:      tape=lowset,reset

Response:    tape/lowsense,footage,fast,capstan,
             stop,tach,
             ready,lcl/rem


Settable parameters:
lowset         if off, tape may run off end of reel. If low (default), end
               of tape will be sensed.
reset          reset to reset footage counter to 0, blank to leave counter
               alone.

Monitor-only parameters:
lowsense       As monitor, this tells whether tape is actually at the low-tape
               point, i.e. off means not at low-tape.
footage        Actual footage counter reading, 5 digits with leading zeroes.
fast           Fast tape switch on front panel, fast or nor.
capstan        capstan moving, or stop has been completed.
stop           stop has been issued, or nonstop.
tach           tach is locked or unlocked, i.e. tape is up to speed.
ready          tape drive vacuum is ready or notready.
lcl/rem        switch setting, rem or lcl.

Comments: 
MAT module functions available.
